---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import GravityScene from '../components/hero/GravityScene';
---

<Layout title="Identity Engineering">
	<main>
		<!-- Hero: Identity Stem -->
		<section class="relative flex flex-col min-h-[100dvh] bg-[#0a0a0f]">
			<div class="shrink-0 z-10 text-center max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 w-full pt-24 md:pt-28 pb-3 md:pb-4">
				<h1 class="text-6xl sm:text-7xl md:text-[5.5rem] lg:text-[6.5rem] font-bold tracking-tighter leading-[0.9] mb-4 md:mb-5 text-white">
					Identity Engineering
				</h1>
				<p class="text-lg md:text-xl lg:text-2xl text-white/50 max-w-2xl mx-auto font-light">
					A science-grounded framework for consciously shaping human identities in the AI era.
				</p>
			</div>

			<div class="relative flex-1 min-h-[52dvh] w-full">
				<GravityScene client:load />
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- Why / Ontology -->
		<section class="py-28 md:py-36 border-t border-white/10">
			<div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-8">
				<div class="text-sm uppercase tracking-[4px] text-white/40 mb-6">Why</div>
				<h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-8 text-white leading-[1.1]">
					Static sameness is no longer enough.
				</h2>
				<div class="space-y-6 text-lg text-white/55 leading-relaxed">
					<p>
						Historically, identity meant <em class="text-white/70 not-italic">identitas</em> —
						sameness: remaining recognizable as the same over time.
						In the AI era that kind of sameness is cheap. Systems can copy, fork, and simulate
						“the same” at scale.
					</p>
					<p>
						Identity Engineering relocates sameness:
						not in the snapshot of who you are now (copyable),
						but in <strong class="text-white/80">Sameness-as-Trajectory</strong> —
						the causal chain of how you change — balanced with
						<strong class="text-white/80">Causal Entropy</strong>:
						maximizing the quality and quantity of future freedom of action.
					</p>
					<p>
						Identity becomes a designable geometric system: a stem through time,
						with mass, curvature, rotation, and forces that act between identities —
						plus disciplines to engineer it.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- Framework overview: descriptive + actionable -->
		<section class="py-28 md:py-36 border-t border-white/10">
			<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-8">
				<div class="text-sm uppercase tracking-[4px] text-white/40 mb-6">Framework</div>
				<h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-6 text-white leading-[1.1] max-w-2xl">
					Descriptive geometry. Actionable practice.
				</h2>
				<p class="text-lg text-white/50 leading-relaxed max-w-2xl mb-16">
					First we describe a single identity, then interaction between identities,
					then the engineering disciplines that make it practice — not only theory.
				</p>

				<div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 md:gap-10">
					<div class="border-t border-white/15 pt-8">
						<div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[3px] text-white/35 mb-4">Descriptive · Single</div>
						<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-3">One identity</h3>
						<p class="text-white/50 leading-relaxed text-base mb-4">
							<strong class="text-white/70">Time</strong> (Identity Stem) as foundation;
							<strong class="text-white/70"> Mass</strong>, <strong class="text-white/70">Curvature</strong>,
							and <strong class="text-white/70">Rotation</strong> as form and stability.
						</p>
						<p class="text-sm text-white/35 leading-relaxed">
							Past = State Differential · Present = State · Future = Vision Gradient
						</p>
					</div>

					<div class="border-t border-white/15 pt-8">
						<div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[3px] text-white/35 mb-4">Descriptive · Interactive</div>
						<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-3">Between identities</h3>
						<p class="text-white/50 leading-relaxed text-base mb-4">
							<strong class="text-white/70">Gravitation</strong> — attraction from a high-mass vision;
							<strong class="text-white/70"> Relativity</strong> — identity only in relation to another observer.
						</p>
						<p class="text-sm text-white/35 leading-relaxed">
							From isolated geometry to forces in a field of others.
						</p>
					</div>

					<div class="border-t border-white/15 pt-8">
						<div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[3px] text-white/35 mb-4">Actionable</div>
						<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-3">Three disciplines</h3>
						<p class="text-white/50 leading-relaxed text-base mb-4">
							<strong class="text-white/70">Vision Engineering</strong> (future),
							<strong class="text-white/70"> Habit Engineering</strong> (present),
							<strong class="text-white/70"> Measurement Engineering</strong> (past) —
							including Questions as Probes.
						</p>
						<p class="text-sm text-white/35 leading-relaxed">
							Temporal practice layers. Own the past · stabilize the present · open the future.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="mt-14">
					<a
						href="/framework"
						class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-8 py-3.5 rounded-full bg-white text-black font-medium hover:bg-white/90 transition"
					>
						Explore the Framework
						<span class="text-black/50">→</span>
					</a>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- Architect shift -->
		<section class="py-24 border-t border-white/10">
			<div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-8 text-center">
				<div class="text-sm uppercase tracking-[4px] text-white/40 mb-6">Shift</div>
				<p class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-medium tracking-tight text-white/90 leading-snug">
					Executor → Author → Architect
				</p>
				<p class="mt-6 text-lg text-white/45 leading-relaxed max-w-xl mx-auto">
					Not only shape your own stem — build language and structures others can use
					to make differentials transparent and vision gradients sharp.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- Big Questions teaser -->
		<section class="py-28 md:py-36 border-t border-white/10">
			<div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-8">
				<div class="text-sm uppercase tracking-[4px] text-white/40 mb-6">Frontier</div>
				<h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-8 text-white leading-[1.1]">
					The map is incomplete on purpose.
				</h2>
				<p class="text-lg text-white/55 leading-relaxed mb-6">
					The framework is grounded in human-scale identity: time, mass, curvature, rotation,
					gravitation, relativity, and the three disciplines.
					That foundation is necessary — not sufficient for every future already becoming plausible.
				</p>
				<p class="text-lg text-white/55 leading-relaxed mb-12">
					Substrate independence, collective scale, AI co-identity, and more —
					questions that cannot yet be fully answered, but must already be asked.
				</p>
				<a
					href="/big-questions"
					class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-8 py-3.5 rounded-full border border-white/20 text-white/80 hover:bg-white/5 hover:text-white transition"
				>
					Big Questions
					<span class="text-white/40">→</span>
				</a>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- Close -->
		<section class="py-24 border-t border-white/10">
			<div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-8 text-center">
				<p class="text-xl text-white/50 mb-10 max-w-lg mx-auto">
					The framework is open. Start with the geometry — or with the frontier.
				</p>
				<div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 justify-center">
					<a href="/framework" class="px-8 py-3.5 rounded-full bg-white text-black font-medium hover:bg-white/90 transition">
						Framework
					</a>
					<a href="/big-questions" class="px-8 py-3.5 rounded-full border border-white/20 text-white/70 hover:bg-white/5 transition">
						Big Questions
					</a>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>
	</main>
</Layout>
